a. Revising the section heading;?></title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d431e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d445e12" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph> When requested by an agency, the
General Services Administration (GSA) will assist <ph rev="FAC 2021-06 July 12, 2021" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2019-001?>in rent, lease, or<?FM MARKER [Why] b. Removing from paragraph (a) introductory text “in lease or” and adding “in rent, lease, or” in its place;?></ph> purchase
decisions by providing information such as-</p>
               <ol id="d431e23" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d445e23" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Pending price
adjustments to Federal Supply Schedule contracts;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d445e28" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Recent or
imminent technological developments;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d445e33" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph> New techniques;
and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d445e38" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph> Industry
or market trends.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d445e43" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  <ph rev="FAC 2021-06 July 12, 2021" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2019-001?>For additional GSA assistance
and guidance, agencies may—<?FM MARKER [Why] c. Revising paragraph (b); and?></ph>
               </p>
               <ol rev="FAC 2021-06 July 12, 2021" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d445e52" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>Request information from the GSA
FAS National Customer Service Center by phone at 1-800-488-3111
or by email at <xref href="mailto:ncsccustomer.service@gsa.gov"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">ncsccustomer.service@gsa.gov</xref>;
and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d445e57" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>See GSA website,
Schedule 51 V Hardware Superstore-Equipment Rental, (<xref href="https://www.gsa.gov/buying-selling/products-services/industrial-products-services/rental-of-industrial-equipment"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">https://www.gsa.gov/buying-selling/products-services/industrial-products-services/rental-of-industrial-equipment</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
